1. copy jmx_prometheus_javaagent-0.18.0.jar and kafka-3_0_0.yml in bin directory

2. Kafka standalone server

KAFKA_CLUSTER_ID="$(sh kafka-storage.sh random-uuid)"
echo $KAFKA_CLUSTER_ID
sh kafka-storage.sh format -t $KAFKA_CLUSTER_ID -c ../config/server.properties
sh kafka-server-start.sh ../config/server.properties --standalone

3. Once after we start the Kafka broker if we launch the http://localhost:8080/metrics url it should show 
    as metrics endpoint with the list of metrics.

4. Start Prometheus sever:
sudo systemctl start prometheus
sudo systemctl status prometheus 
Access interface using default URL http://localhost:9090/

5. Start Graphana Server:
sudo systemctl start grafana-server
Graphana login URL   http://localhost:3000/login  (default user:admin, password:admin123)

Note : if password is not working, please try
sudo grafana-cli admin reset-admin-password <new-password>
sudo systemctl restart grafana-server

6. In Graphana, create a datasource -> Prometheus 

7. There is default Kafka Grafna dashboard called Kafka Overview already available we can import this into our grafana web. 
    Copy Kafka Overview dashboard id from this url https://grafana.com/grafana/dashboards/11962-kafka-metrics/. Import to grafana with id
    (In Dashboard -> New -> import -> https://grafana.com/grafana/dashboards/721 ; select datasource -> Prometheus)
    
    








